{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":5583,"name":"","username":"practicing01","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/p/b5e925/{size}.png","created_at":"2015-03-27T14:13:32.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello, I need walls to be in one group, players in another (that will collide with walls but not collide with other players) and I need to do a physics raycast that will hit the walls but not the players.  What layer/mask combo do I need to specify for walls and players in the editor?  How do I calculate the unsigned int mask needed by the raycast method?  Thanks for any help. Edit: Thanks, that worked.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:04:27.302Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":209,"reads":74,"readers_count":73,"score":1061.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":957,"topic_slug":"how-do-you-choose-collision-masks-layers-solved","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://discourse.urho3d.io/t/the-concept-of-collisionlayer-and-collisionmask-about-physics/3352/2","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"The Concept of CollisionLayer and CollisionMask about Physics","clicks":9},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/collisions-ohysics-for-missiles-bullets-explosions-etc/4771/74","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"Collisions (ohysics) for Missiles, Bullets, Explosions etc","clicks":6},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/setcollisioneventmode-seems-to-be-static/3573/5","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"SetCollisionEventMode seems to be static?","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":140,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":13065,"name":"Justin Miller","username":"jmiller","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jmiller/{size}/2367_2.png","created_at":"2016-08-05T04:37:17.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eBecause this thread deserved its answers, even if \u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/practicing01\"\u003e@practicing01\u003c/a\u003e lurksâ€¦\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e#include \u0026lt;Urho3D/Container/FlagSet.h\u0026gt;\n\nenum class Flag : unsigned int {\n  none = 0\n  , env = (1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 0), obj = (1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 1), character = (1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 2), particle = (1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 3), projectile = (1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 4)\n  , all = Urho3D::M_MAX_UNSIGNED\n};\n/* bit shift expression to binary (digits presumably corresponding to editor checkboxes)\n1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 0 == 000001 (01) \n1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 1 == 000010 (02) \n1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 2 == 000100 (04) \n1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 3 == 001000 (08) \n1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 4 == 010000 (16) \n1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; 5 == 100000 (32) \n*/\n\n// Using Urho3D FlagSet without macros.\nnamespace Urho3D {\n  /// Type trait which enables Enum to be used as FlagSet template parameter. Bitwise operators (| \u0026amp; ^ ~) over enabled Enum will result in FlagSet\u0026lt;Enum\u0026gt;.\n  template\u0026lt;\u0026gt; struct IsFlagSet\u0026lt;ObjectLayer\u0026gt; {\n    inline static constexpr bool value_ = true;\n  };\n}\nusing Flags = Urho3D::FlagSet\u0026lt;Flag\u0026gt;;\n\n// ...\n\n// Raycast query for not character or particle or pickup or projectile.\nFlags viewMask(~(Flag::character|Flag::particle|Flag::pickup|Flag::projectile));\n\nRayOctreeQuery query(results, revRay, RAY_TRIANGLE, distance, DRAWABLE_GEOMETRY, viewMask);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-11-05T06:44:53.351Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":73,"readers_count":72,"score":54.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":957,"topic_slug":"how-do-you-choose-collision-masks-layers-solved","display_username":"Justin Miller","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":21,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":20809,"name":"é­”å¤§å†œ ğğğ³ ç¾æ‹›èœ","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2017-09-17T16:47:22.915Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eYou could also add the following constexpr somewhere:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003econstexpr unsigned Layer(unsigned x) { return 1 \u0026lt;\u0026lt; (x - 1); }\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis would allow you to write \u003ccode\u003eLayer(1) + Layer(3)\u003c/code\u003e, for example, to create a layer mask.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-09-18T01:48:24.762Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":62,"readers_count":61,"score":72.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":957,"topic_slug":"how-do-you-choose-collision-masks-layers-solved","display_username":"é­”å¤§å†œ ğğğ³ ç¾æ‹›èœ","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"username":"jmiller","name":"Justin Miller","avatar_template":